45	Your project is facing both budget pressure and timeline constraints. Due to unexpected technical complexity, you're projecting a 15% budget overrun and a 3-week schedule delay. Which approach should you prioritize?	Focus on reducing scope and features to Meet the original timeline, accepting the budget overrun as a necessary cost of maintaining the schedule commitment.	Negotiate additional funding to cover the budget-overrun while accepting the 3-week schedule delay the as the trade-off for staying within scope.	Implement cost-reduction measures first to address the budget overrun, then work on schedule compression techniques to minimize the timeline impact.	Seek a balanced approach that partially addresses both issues, accepting smaller overruns in both budget and schedule rather than fully solving either. 		C	PMBOK 7 emphasizes leadership behaviors, team empowerment, and decision-making to guide projects effectively. Demonstrate Leadership Behaviors, pp. 40–43.
