199	A project team in a digital marketing project discovers that their key design software license has expired, halting the team work on a critical campaign visuals. What is the most effective initial action for the project manager to take?	Request that the team manually sketch the campaign concepts while awaiting license renewal	Have the team work with the IT department to renew the license	Prioritize other aspects of the campaign that don't require design software the software icons	Coordinate with the IT department to promptly renew the software license		D	PMBOK 7 emphasizes leadership behaviors, team empowerment, and decision-making to guide projects effectively. Demonstrate Leadership Behaviors, pp. 40–43.
200	During a critical phase of a software development project, a key developer notifies the project manager that they will need to take an unexpected leave, impacting the completion of a crucial backlog item scheduled for demonstration in the upcoming sprint review. What should the project manager do?	insist that the developer work remotely during their leave to ensure the backlog item is completed on time	Escalate the issue to senior management and demand that they assign an additional resource immediately	Reevaluate the sprint goals and backlog priorities, consult with the team about adjustments, and communicate the revised plan to stakeholders	Cancel the upcoming sprint review, citing the lack of progress on the crucial backlog item		C	PMBOK 7 recommends tailoring project approaches, methods, and practices according to project context and environment. Tailor Based on Context, pp. 44–46.